post_text:
Congratulations to Peter Larson, who broke two state high school swimming records on March 2—19.97 in the 50 free and 43.46 in the 100 free.

Peter, who attended MNOHS full-time for two years and now attends part-time, competes for Edina High School and was the first Minnesota high schooler to break 20 seconds in the 50 free. Peter joins his brother on the state record board; JohnThomas Larson, who graduated from MNOHS, set records in the 200 IM and 500 Free, competing for MNOHS at the time.

Next year, Peter will join John Thomas at the University of Texas, swimming for the top Division 1 program in the country, under the top Division 1 coach in the country, greatest of all time Eddie Reese. That’s Peter in the photos wearing Edina’s green colors last week and John Thomas in 2017 sporting a stylish MNOHS swim cap!
text:
Congratulations to Peter Larson, who broke two state high school swimming records on March 2—19.97 in the 50 free and 43.46 in the 100 free.

Peter, who attended MNOHS full-time for two years and now attends part-time, competes for Edina High School and was the first Minnesota high schooler to break 20 seconds in the 50 free. Peter joins his brother on the state record board; JohnThomas Larson, who graduated from MNOHS, set records in the 200 IM and 500 Free, competing for MNOHS at the time.

Next year, Peter will join John Thomas at the University of Texas, swimming for the top Division 1 program in the country, under the top Division 1 coach in the country, greatest of all time Eddie Reese. That’s Peter in the photos wearing Edina’s green colors last week and John Thomas in 2017 sporting a stylish MNOHS swim cap!
